DISPLAY SALARY

AIM:
Write a PL/SQL program for display of salary of an employee

ALGORITHM:
Step1: Start
Step2: Declare variable rid and sal
Step3: Enter the value of rid
Step4: Select the salary from the table employee where the employee id equals to rid
Step5: Assign the salary to sal
Step6: Display the salary in sal
Step7: Stop


QUERIES:

CREATE TABLE EMPLOYEE
(
EMP_ID NUMBER(20),
SALARY NUMBER(20)
);

INSERT INTO EMPLOYEE VALUES(101,20000);
INSERT INTO EMPLOYEE VALUES(102,10000);
INSERT INTO EMPLOYEE VALUES(103,15000);
INSERT INTO EMPLOYEE VALUES(104,9000);


CODE

DECLARE
RID INTEGER;
SAL INTEGER;
BEGIN
RID:=&RID;
SELECT SALARY INTO SAL
FROM EMPLOYEE
WHERE EMP_ID=RID;
DBMS_OUTPUT.PUT_LINE('Salary is:'||SAL);

END;
/
